%% Flow: execution session lifecycle — timer fire to clean shutdown.
%% Last updated: 2026-07-21 (Nexus JWT removed)
sequenceDiagram
    participant T as Timer/Trigger
    participant W as wake.sh
    participant G as Gate Chain
    participant P as Pre-launch
    participant C as claude -p
    participant M as Memory/State

    T->>W: fire (nightly / emergency / manual)
    W->>G: Gate 0: check_usage.sh
    alt usage exceeded
        G-->>W: abort
    end

    alt TRIGGER_MODE=nightly
        W->>G: Gate 1: emergency_mode.active flag
        W->>G: Gate 2: window + trigger vs session_schedule.json
        alt outside windows or locked
            G-->>W: abort
        end
    end

    W->>G: Gate 4 (all modes): session.lock
    alt locked
        G-->>W: abort
    end

    W->>P: write lock, increment counter
    P->>P: behavioral_adapter.py → behavioral_context.txt
    P->>P: resolve_session_type.py → session type + augmented goal
    alt philosophy_cap (consecutive ≥ 3)
        P-->>W: abort — skip launch
    end
    P->>P: loom session start → current_loom_session_id.txt

    P->>C: launch with augmented goal + persona
    C->>M: read latest_summary.md + learnings_digest.md
    C->>C: orient → work tasks (check context/time between tasks)

    C->>M: write latest_summary.md (HOT STATE)
    C->>M: update progress.md, learnings.md, index.md
    C->>M: write sessions/YYYY-MM-DD_N.md
    C->>M: append session_log.csv
    C->>M: analytics_write.py → analytics.db
    C->>M: session_report.py → state/reports/
    C->>M: loom session end --handoff

    C-->>W: exit
    W->>W: update consecutive_philosophy.count
    W->>W: relationship_update.py (post-session, non-fatal)
    W->>W: remove session.lock
